        <num>CCP 3462</num>
        <heading>3462.  Partition of succession property</heading>
        <content>
          <p>Art. 3462.  Partition of succession property
When a succession has been opened judicially, the coheirs and legatees of the deceased cannot petition for a partition of the succession property unless they could at that time be sent into possession of the succession under Articles 3001, 3004, 3006, 3061, 3361, 3362, 3371, 3372, or 3381.</p>
        </content>
